Therefore, it is difficult to determine what awareness may look like in other animals.
If, as something internal and subjective, it can neither be measured nor, because of the special hardware, analyzed on the basis of our own experience, his exploration presents us with great problems.
Most of my remarks relate to the content of conscious experience, but there is another aspect of consciousness that should be more scientifically accessible.
One could examine the consciousness processes of animals without regard to their content, and this is exactly what happens in studies on the short-term memory of primates, especially the example of visualization.
