In the umbilical cord, which was formerly considered a biomedical waste, there is rich blood on stem cells, which can serve to treat serious diseases, such as leukemia.
`A few weeks ago we celebrated the storage of our thousandth umbilical cord blood sample, and we plan to take more than a thousand annually.
`We should probably start making it available for transplants early next year,' explains Dr. Décary continues, which describes this program of cord blood loss as very popular.
